<br>
What is a &quot;lie&quot;?  Who determines what is the &quot;truth&quot;?  You are asking about a concept that is almost as abstract and as debatable as human existence...<br>
<br>
Suppose, Crylin tells Optimius a &quot;lie&quot;... Optimus believes this &quot;lie&quot; to be the &quot;truth&quot; then Optimus continues to tell this once &quot;lie&quot; now transformed into the &quot;truth&quot; to everyone is Optimus lying?<br>
<br>
Technically, No he is not Lying...  Lying is presenting false information with the INTENT to decieve.  Optimius is Not lying technically...but then the next logical question is what exactly is Opi doing?<br>
<br>
Is Opi telling the truth? Truth is a statement proven to be or accepted as true.  True is Consisent with fact or reality.  So, lets say what Opi is telling everyone spreads like wildfire, with everyone who speaks this statement believing it to be true this once &quot;lie&quot; can now be a universal truth, so much so that the original statement of Crylin to Opi has been transformed into from a once &quot;lie&quot; into the &quot;truth&quot;.<br>
<br>
Truth and lies are subjective and objective concepts all at once.<br>
<br>
One &quot;lie&quot; that has been transformed into the truth, is the Holocaust...  Scream, fight, and yell or you want, but it is feking a LIE that 8 million Jews died during the Holocaust, the numbers are a flat out LIE.  I am not saying the holocaust did not happen, all I am saying is not as many people died as they say...<br>
<br>
Governments DO NOT lie to their people, people lie to themselves...Because they are either to ignorant or just do not care...Quite circular arrangement...<br>
<br>
Uncle Sam tells Average American Iraq had WMD.  Proving this statement is NOT BASED on finding WMD, but based on whether or not the American public embraces the statement of Iraq sas WMD as true, if so, this statement is now the truth.  <br>
<br>
In conclusion, Truth is not a fact, nothing in this world is a fact... To paraphrase my friend orwell from 1984  2+2=5 cause we say it does.<br>
<br>
Crylin<br>
<br>
